<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEDFFEC2580F8EEFE7CF87F" author="Loew, H." box="[255,386,1904,1931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="234 - 242" refId="ref8276" refString="Loew, H. (1865) Ueber einige bei Kutais in Imeretien gefangene Dipteren. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift, 9, 234 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 18650090307" type="journal article" year="1865">Loew 1865</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEDFFEC24F2F8EEFDBFF87F" author="Syrovatka, O." box="[397,577,1905,1931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka 1991</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEDFFEC272CF8EDFD28F87F" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[595,726,1905,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEDFFEC272CF8EDFD28F87F" box="[595,726,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">Empis hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Caucasus and locally quite common occurring over a broad range of altitudes from submontane area closer the shores of the Black Sea up to 
<quantity id="30559B7DFFEDFFEC2039F80AFA62F844" box="[1350,1436,1941,1968]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" unit="m" value="1600.0">1600 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEDFFEC25E0F826FE32F827" author="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V." box="[159,460,1977,2003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="170 - 184" refId="ref8188" refString="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V. (2014) A review of dance-flies of the Empis (s. str.) pennipes group of species (Diptera: Empididae) from the Caucasus, with descriptions of five new species. Caucasian Entomological Bulletin, 10, 170 - 184. [in Russian, partly English] https: // doi. org / 10.23885 / 1814 - 3326 - 2014 - 10 - 1 - 170 - 184" type="journal article" year="2014">Kustov &amp; Shamshev 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEDFFEC24A1F826FD5FF827" author="Syrovatka, O." box="[478,673,1977,2003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka (1991)</bibRefCitation>
re-described 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEDFFEC2645F825FC71F827" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[826,911,1977,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEDFFEC2645F825FCB5F827" box="[826,843,1978,2003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEDFFEC2626F826FC71F827" box="[857,911,1977,2003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and designated the 
<typeStatus id="2816883AFFEDFFEC2112F826FB29F827" box="[1133,1239,1977,2003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">lectotype</typeStatus>
, but he compared this species only with 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEDFFEC24E9F841FC41F803" authority="Loew. Unfortunately, Syrovatka (1991)" authorityName="Loew. Unfortunately, Syrovatka" authorityYear="1991" box="[406,959,2013,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEDFFEC24E9F841FE59F803" box="[406,423,2014,2039]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEDFFEC24C9F842FE04F803" box="[438,506,2013,2039]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">pilosa</emphasis>
Loew. Unfortunately, 
<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEDFFEC2784F842FC41F803" author="Syrovatka, O." box="[763,959,2013,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka (1991)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
omitted in his re-descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEDFFEC2043F841FA7CF803" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1340,1410,2014,2039]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEDFFEC2043F841FA7CF803" box="[1340,1410,2014,2039]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">Empis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="DEEA57F1FFEDFFEF20F5F841FF47FF47" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="272" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
characters such as the setosity of the prosternum. 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEEFFEF2797FF05FC94FF47" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[744,874,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF2797FF05FC94FF47" box="[744,874,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">Empis hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the prosternum setose. The male terminalia of 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEEFFEF25E8FF21FF13FF23" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,237,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF25E8FF21FF56FF23" box="[151,168,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF25C8FF22FF13FF23" box="[183,237,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEEFFEF2459FF21FE38FF23" box="[294,454,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropilosa">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF2459FF21FEC9FF23" box="[294,311,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF2439FF22FE38FF23" box="[326,454,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">nigropilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear identical (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEEFFEF27B6FF22FC75FF23" author="Collin, J. E." box="[713,907,189,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" pagination="385 - 420" refId="ref7967" refString="Collin, J. E. (1960) Some Empididae from Palestine. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (13), 2, 385 - 420. [1959] https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222935908650872" type="journal article" year="1960">Collin 1960: 142</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3; 
<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEEFFEF269CFF22FB2CFF23" author="Syrovatka, O." box="[995,1234,188,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka 1991: 255</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 10A; 
<bibRefCitation id="933C4B69FFEEFFEF2034FF22FE5DFF0F" author="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V." pageId="6" pageNumber="272" pagination="170 - 184" refId="ref8188" refString="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V. (2014) A review of dance-flies of the Empis (s. str.) pennipes group of species (Diptera: Empididae) from the Caucasus, with descriptions of five new species. Caucasian Entomological Bulletin, 10, 170 - 184. [in Russian, partly English] https: // doi. org / 10.23885 / 1814 - 3326 - 2014 - 10 - 1 - 170 - 184" type="journal article" year="2014">Kustov &amp; Shamshev 2014: 181</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 10) and the majority of other external characters match. However, 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEEFFEF21B3FF7DFA92FF0F" box="[1228,1388,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropilosa">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF21B3FF7DFB23FF0F" box="[1228,1245,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF2193FF7EFA92FF0F" box="[1260,1388,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">nigropilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEEFFEF2479FE99FEA5FEEB" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[262,347,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF2479FE99FEE9FEEB" box="[262,279,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF245AFE9AFEA5FEEB" box="[293,347,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bare prosternum (vs. setose), four scutellar setae (vs. 6–12), somewhat sparser and longer anteroventral setae on the hind femur and faintly infuscate wing (vs. brownish).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F7123698FFEEFFEF25B8FED2FA99FE5B" blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">
It should be noted that some characters of 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEEFFEF27CEFED1FCF6FE93" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[689,776,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF27CEFED1FD3CFE93" box="[689,706,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF27ADFED2FCF6FE93" box="[722,776,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very variable, e.g., body size (
<quantity id="30559B7DFFEEFFEF21E8FED3FADAFE93" box="[1175,1316,332,359]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" unit="mm" value="5.05" valueMax="5.6" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.6 mm</quantity>
, the lectotype— 
<quantity id="30559B7DFFEEFFEF259BFEEFFEC2FE7F" box="[228,316,368,395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" unit="mm" value="5.6">5.6 mm</quantity>
); number of notopleural setae (3–5, usually 3–4, in the 
<typeStatus id="2816883AFFEEFFEF26E2FEEEFBFAFE7F" box="[925,1028,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">lectotype</typeStatus>
4); number and robustness of scutellar setae (6–12, when 6 or 8 then 4 usually stronger); prosternum sometimes only with 1–3 setae on each side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F7123698FFEEFFEF25B8FE26FF18FE03" blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">
I provisionally retain 
<taxonomicName id="30AD4D1BFFEEFFEF24C6FE25FDA6FE27" box="[441,600,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropilosa">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF24C6FE25FE34FE27" box="[441,458,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF24A7FE26FDA6FE27" box="[472,600,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">nigropilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species until additional material becomes available from that region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BFB76513FFEEFFEF25B8FD9FFDCAFDEF" box="[199,564,512,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F7123698FFEEFFEF25B8FD9FFDCAFDEF" blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" box="[199,564,512,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="C5D9EA8AFFEEFFEF25B8FD9FFE9FFDEF" bold="true" box="[199,353,512,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palaearctic: 
<collectingCountry id="8FBA7608FFEEFFEF248EFD9EFDCEFDEF" box="[497,560,513,539]" name="Syria" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">Syria</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
